                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <emph>recommended:</emph> from David Hume's <title level="m">Treatise on
                                Human Nature</title> (on the origin of ideas) * </item>
                    </list>

                    <p rend="noCount">Wed. 9/10 – ecology and interconnectedness</p>
                    <list type="unordered">
                        <item>
                            <list type="unordered">
                                <item>“Lines Written in Early Spring”—William Wordsworth *</item>
                                <item>“Mouse’s Nest” – John Clare *</item>
                                <item>“This Lime-tree Bower, my Prison”—S.T. Coleridge #</item>
                                <item>from “Preface to <title level="m">Lyrical
                                    Ballads</title>”—William Wordsworth (“The principle Object,
                                    then…”) #</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <list type="unordered">
                                <item>“Corson’s Inlet” A. R. Ammons #</item>
                                <item>“Gopher Guts” (song)—Aesop Rock #</item>
                                <item><title level="m">Magnolia</title> (movie) °</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                    </list>

                    <p rend="noCount">Wed. 9/17 – melancholy vs. negative capability</p>
                    <list type="unordered">
                        <item>
                            <list type="unordered">
                                <item>“Anactoria”—Algernon Charles Swinburne * </item>
                                <item>from “A Contribution to the Psychogenesis of Manic-Depressive
                                    States”—Melanie Klein# </item>
                                <item>music from Bob Dylan, Sufjan Stevens # </item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
